name: src/from/StreamFromCallable.js
StreamFromCallable
description: Class that wraps a callable with a stream.

name: constructor
description: The constructor. Stores the callable that yields values to stream.

name: read
description:
Returns the next token in the stream or {@link StreamFromCallable#eof}
if the stream has been exhausted.

name: unread
description:
Puts a token back in the stream. If {@link StreamFromCallable#read} is
used just after, this token will be returned.

params.name: token
params.description: The token to put back in the stream.

name: ./doc/manual/installation.md
content:
# Installation

Can be managed using
[jspm](http://jspm.io)
or [npm](https://github.com/npm/npm).

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@aureooms/js-stream
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @aureooms/js-stream --save
```
